##################################################################################### ReplicaSet

the replicaset which manages the pods when a pod is unavaiable or crash it will managed by replicaset it will create new pod.
in the replicaSet also we have major configurations like

apiversion:
kind:
metadata:

spec:
  template:
                     the template which is the information of the pod to mainatain , what is the use of template is when a pod is crashed so at that time replicaset need to create new pod so for that we need exact information so it will take infomration from template with same configuration.
replicas:                 we will define how many replica need to present for that application
selector:
    matchlabels:
    type:           this is like which application should be maintained and what is major advantage is when we create a pod with out replicaset and that pod has a type which is defined in 
                    metadata if we mention that name in the selector the replicaset will take care of that pod also , when that pod is crash or deleted the repilcaset will create or mainatain that pod.


to increase the replicaset we have multiple ways like updating the yaml file or 
+++ kubectl scale rs --replicaset name --replicaset=6 
++ kubectl get replicaset 
++ kubectl delete replicaset myapp-replicaset  

---- ReplicaSet ensures a fixed number of pods are running.
  --- Deployment manages ReplicaSets and provides rolling updates, rollback, and version control

