############## taint & tolerations

taint & tolerations are used to set restrictions on what pods can be scheduled on node.
taint is added to node 
like which pod to be created in that node 
toleration is pods 
creation of taint to a node
+++++ kubectl taint node --node name --key=value:effect 
to remove the taint also same command at the end we need to add "-" symbol
+++  kubectl taint node --node name --key=value:effect-

nodeseclector =====
nodeselector is used for which pod is need to be creadted in which nodes
like we have 3 nodes 1,2,3 the 1 node is bigger and other two are small so now pods will create randomly in any node but the pod requirement is high so for this problem we use the nodeselector
we will define nodeselector when we creating a new pod 
in yaml file we define 

nodeselector :
    size:large 

before this we need to check the node size or change the size 
++++ kubectl label node --node name <key=value>
kubectl label node node-1 size=large
